menu "qremote"

config QREMOTE_HAS_DISPLAY
    bool "Enable AMOLED display output (Waveshare 1.64\" SH8601)"
    default n
    help
        When enabled, pulls in LVGL + esp_lcd_sh8601 and shows network
        status + incoming OSC messages on the 280x456 AMOLED. Intended
        for the waveshare_amoled PlatformIO env. The feathers3 env has
        no display, so this should remain disabled there.

endmenu
